<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="413" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 702.6211/221.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">German Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt of your note of the 21st instant in which you state that if
                            the case against Consul Müller at Seattle could be discontinued you
                            would be quite ready to take into consideration his transfer to some
                            other post in the United States.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have the honor to say that the Department has by telegraph
                            communicated with the Governor of the State of Washington with a view to
                            bringing about the dismissal of the proceedings against Consul Müller,
                            such action having been based on the understanding that steps will be
                            promptly taken by your Government to transfer Mr. Müller to a post in
                            some other State.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>